    <p>In the video example above, besides the Harmonic minor scale itself, I snuck in the G natural from the original unaltered Aeolian mode and one instance of D# which is a very dissonant sounding sharp 4th interval just to give the whole passage a little more edge. Inserting these notes that don’t belong in a musical phrase can sound super awesome but it must be done carefully. These in-between notes are sometimes called passing tones since we just use them to “pass” between the others…never really landing on them and hanging out there for too long. More on that coming soon in future lessons!

